    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is a known gap in our API (IIRC we have other open issues about it).\r\n\r\ntransform is by definition done column wise. I don't think that's likely to change.\r\n\r\nI'd recommend something like\r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [3]: df.groupby('c').apply(lambda df: pd.Series(df.a.sum() / df.b.sum(), index=df.index, name='ratio'))\r\nOut[3]:\r\nc\r\nq  0    0.294118\r\n   1    0.294118\r\n   2    0.294118\r\n   3    0.294118\r\nw  4    0.478261\r\n   5    0.478261\r\nName: ratio, dtype: float64\r\n```\r\n\r\nfor now. In the future some kind of `.apply_table` or `.apply(func, axis=None)` may be possible."
  },
