    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It doesn't avoid a temporary, but FWIW, I write these type of things with a named groupby - if perf matters, probably faster than @TomAugspurger showed because it will take vectorized paths.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [32]: gb = df.groupby('c')\r\n\r\nIn [33]: df['ab_weighted'] = gb['a'].transform('sum') / gb['b'].transform('sum')\r\n\r\nIn [34]: df\r\nOut[34]: \r\n   a   b  c  ab_weighted\r\n0  1   7  q     0.294118\r\n1  2   8  q     0.294118\r\n2  3   9  q     0.294118\r\n3  4  10  q     0.294118\r\n4  5  11  w     0.478261\r\n5  6  12  w     0.478261\r\n```\r\n"
  },
